HEADWORD: Tempean
<hw>Tem*pe"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Temple, a valley in Thessaly, celebrated by Greek poets on account of
its beautiful scenery; resembling Temple; hence, beautiful; delightful;
charming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Temper</ent>⟦br⟧
